AB  - Coalitions are usually defined with respect to a static framework of dependencies among agents. In this paper we propose a dynamic view of dependence networks to enable dynamic coalitions which can self adapt to a situation by exploiting the possibility to trigger other agents' goals. © 2008 IEEE.
