AB  - Various features needed to built characters that are able to establish an empathic relation with users are discussed. Proximity factor is used for a synthetic character to evoke affective and cognitive empathy, user must feel close to the character. Proximity factor is based on the fact that children are found to respond more empathically to those that are perceived as similar to the self than those who are perceived as dissimilar. This appears to be the case when similarity is defined in terms of shared characteristics, such as sex, race or in term of shared personal experiences.
